                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18211205-8-victim162 t18211205-8-viclabel47"></join>, and lives in <placeName id="t18211205-8-crimeloc48">Cheapside</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18211205-8-crimeloc48" type="placeName" value="Cheapside"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18211205-8-crimeloc48" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18211205-8-off45 t18211205-8-crimeloc48"></join>. On Monday evening, the 9th of November, between seven and eight o'clock, I saw a man put his hand inside the door and take a piece of cloth. I ran to the door, and while I was looking round, the prisoner was brought in; he gave me the cloth from under his frock, it measured four and a half yards, - it laid about two yards inside the door.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18211205-8-person165">
                  CHARLES 
                  ROULEY
               <interp inst="t18211205-8-person165" type="surname" value="ROULEY"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18211205-8-person165" type="given" value="CHARLES"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18211205-8-person165" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I work at Mr. Cleobury's. On the 19th of November, I was coming from one of his shops, to the shop the cloth was stolen from, and saw the prisoner catch the cloth from near the door, he ran across the way, I brought him back, he pulled it from under his frock.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18211205-8-person166">
                  GEORGE 
                  WATTS
               <interp inst="t18211205-8-person166" type="surname" value="WATTS"></interp>
